data.value:
Welcome to Deskbooru
~ Search Panel Tab ~
Search up tags within the search box and click the magnifying glass. Pictures will be displayed that has contained the tag. Simply click the number on the bottom or the next button to go to the next page to view the other pictures/images.
~ Add Images Tab ~
Browse lets you choose a picture from your desktop or an external storage device and will display the file name next to it. The picture will show on the right side.
Add Tag lets you have place any sorts of tags you want to be applied to the picture/image. This will not be fully applied to the picture/image until the "Submit Image" is clicked.
You can delete a tag if you accidentally added a tag by deleting it in the current tags section.
~ Add Folder Tab ~
Browse lets you choose a folder of picture/images that you want to include/imported
The folder-wide tag lets you apply tags to every picture/images within the folder.
Add Tag will allow you to apply a tag to a single picture/image which is shown on the right.
The current tags section will show all the tags for the picture that is shown on the right.
Nothing is finalized until "Submit Image" is clicked. You can delete tags by erasing the tags that is in the "current tags" and " Folder-wide tag" section
